Cell.Text: You made it out alive, at least.
Really? That seems hard to believe. You're sure about that?

Node.Caption: MQ201DelphineOutroA1: The Thalmor don't know anything about the dragons either.

Cell.Text: You're right, you're right. I just... I was sure it must have been them. If not the Thalmor, who? Or... what?

Node.Caption: MQ201DelphineOutroB1: Why'd you send me if you weren't going to believe me?

Cell.Text: <<Shared>> Esbern? He's alive? I thought the Thalmor must have got him years ago. That crazy old man... | Figures the Thalmor would be on his trail, though, if they were trying to figure out what's going on with the dragons.

Node.Caption: MQ201DelphineOutroB2: Yes, I'm sure. They're looking for someone named Esbern.

Cell.Text: <<Shared>> Esbern? He's alive? I thought the Thalmor must have got him years ago. That crazy old man... | Figures the Thalmor would be on his trail, though, if they were trying to figure out what's going on with the dragons.

Node.Caption: MQ201DelphineOutroC1: I don't know, but the Thalmor are looking for someone named Esbern.

Cell.Text: You mean, aside from wanting to kill every Blade they can lay their hands on? | Esbern was one of the Blades archivists, back before the Thalmor smashed us during the Great War. | He knew everything about the ancient dragonlore of the Blades. | Obsessed with it, really. Nobody paid much attention back then. I guess he wasn't as crazy as we all thought.

Node.Caption: MQ201DelphineOutro2Topic: What would the Thalmor want with Esbern?

Cell.Text: Ironic, right? The old enemies assume that every calamity must be a plot by the other side... | Even so, we've got to find Esbern before they do. He'll know how to stop the dragons if anybody does. | Do they know where he is?

Node.Caption: MQ201DelphineOutro2A1: So the Thalmor think the Blades know about the dragons...

Cell.Text: Riften, eh? Probably down in the Ratway, then. It's where I'd go.

Node.Caption: MQ201DelphineOutro2A2: They seem to think he's hiding out in Riften.

Cell.Text: You'd better get to Riften. Ask around the Slaughtered Fop, in the Ratway. It's at least a good starting point.
You'd better get to Riften. Talk to Brynjolf. He's... well-connected. A good starting point at least.
Oh, and when you find Esbern... if you think I'm paranoid... you may have some trouble getting him to trust you. | Just ask him where he was on the 30th of Frostfall. He'll know what it means.
